<!--
	Ref.: https://github.com/snaekobbi/system/releases/tag/v1.2.2
	Tested using BRF output.
	
	Compare output with `(formatter:liblouis)`,
	and output with `(formatter:dotify)`.
	
	Issues with liblouis:
	* Page numbers are positioned to the right of the first line of frontmatter.
	  Expected is that they appear in the top margin (header).
	* There are two page breaks between frontmatter and bodymatter.
	  Expected is that page-break-after and page-break-before collapse into one.
	* The top-center pagenum with ID pg1 is rendered hard left.
	
	Issues with dotify:
	* A print page number is positioned to the right of the first line of frontmatter.
	  Expected is that it appears in the top margin (header).
	  Except that frontmatter contains no print page numbers and should not render any.
	* There are two page breaks between frontmatter and bodymatter.
	  Expected is that page-break-after and page-break-before collapse into one.
	* Braille page numbers are not rendered.
	* The top-center pagenum with ID pg1 is rendered hard left.
-->
<head>
<style type="text/css">
@page {
	size: 35 28;
	@top-center {
		content: string(print-page);
	}
	@top-right {
		content: counter(page);
	}
}
pagenum {
	display: none;
	string-set: print-page content();
}
frontmatter, bodymatter {
	display: block;
	page-break-before: always;
	page-break-after: always;
}
level1, h1, p {
	display: block;
}
</style>
</head>
<book>
<frontmatter>
<doctitle>Pagination test</doctitle>
<docauthor>Davy Kager</docauthor>
</frontmatter>
<bodymatter>
<level1>
<pagenum page="normal" id="pg1">1</pagenum>
<h1>First Page</h1>
<p>This is text on the first print page.</p>
<p>The print page number should be rendered top-center, the braille page number top-right.</p>
</level1>
</bodymatter>
</book>
</dtbook>
